relevant_findings.description: Internal memorandum discussing potential REDSKIN Agent Candidates and psychological assessment process
relevant_findings.direct_quote: Proposal for A&E Assessment of Potential REDSKIN Agent Candidates
relevant_findings.significance: Reveals internal CIA recruitment and screening procedures for covert operatives during early 1960s

relevant_findings.description: Detailed interdepartmental communication about personnel screening and documentation
relevant_findings.direct_quote: It was further ascertained at this time that Mr. Howard OSBORNE desired that all training and assessment of REDSKIN Agents who pass the initial screening be conducted
relevant_findings.significance: Shows high-level oversight of sensitive personnel selection process by senior CIA officials

relevant_findings.description: Document discusses plans for REESKIN Agents processing and training
relevant_findings.direct_quote: SR Division plans to process thirty or thirty-five REESKIN Agents this year. Time is, of course, of the essence, in view of the fact that these people will have to be assessed, security-cleared, briefed, and trained, and arrangements for grants made before the summer season.
relevant_findings.significance: Suggests covert agent training program active during period of interest, potential connection to intelligence operations

relevant_findings.direct_quote: outside the Washington, D.C. area. Most of the training will be conducted in an SR safe house in New York. The representative will probably request a safe house in Baltimore for the final assessment and processing of REESKIN agents
relevant_findings.significance: Indicates multiple secure locations used for agent preparation, potential operational infrastructure
